b'[<p><i><b>UFC Fight Night: Florian vs. Gomi</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC Fight Night 21</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> on March 31, 2010 at <a href="/wiki/Bojangles%27_Coliseum" title="Bojangles\' Coliseum">Bojangles\' Coliseum</a> in <a href="/wiki/Charlotte,_North_Carolina" title="Charlotte, North Carolina">Charlotte, North Carolina</a>,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-UFN21_2-0"><a href="#cite_note-UFN21-2">[2]</a></sup>  This was the third time the UFC held an event in Charlotte, but the first since <a href="/wiki/UFC_5" title="UFC 5">UFC 5</a>.\n</p>, <p>The event was the third UFC event in under two weeks along with <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_LIVE:_Vera_vs._Jones" title="UFC LIVE: Vera vs. Jones">UFC LIVE: Vera vs. Jones</a> and <a href="/wiki/UFC_111" title="UFC 111">UFC 111</a>.  The event also served as the lead-in program for <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/The_Ultimate_Fighter_11" title="The Ultimate Fighter 11">The Ultimate Fighter 11</a>.\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Cole_Miller" title="Cole Miller">Cole Miller</a> was scheduled to face <a href="/wiki/Andre_Winner" title="Andre Winner">Andre Winner</a>, but was forced from the card with an injury and replaced by <a href="/wiki/Rafaello_Oliveira" title="Rafaello Oliveira">Rafaello Oliveira</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>A brief <a href="/wiki/Power_outage" title="Power outage">blackout</a> occurred in the <a href="/wiki/Bojangles%27_Coliseum" title="Bojangles\' Coliseum">Bojangles\' Coliseum</a> when <a href="/wiki/Roy_Nelson_(fighter)" title="Roy Nelson (fighter)">Roy Nelson</a> vs. <a href="/wiki/Stefan_Struve" title="Stefan Struve">Stefan Struve</a> was being announced.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>Fighters were awarded $30,000 bonuses.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-bonus_6-0"><a href="#cite_note-bonus-6">[5]</a></sup>\n</p>]'